  "prompt": "What do I do if my best friend is dating my crush?",
  "response": "Navigating the situation where your best friend is dating your crush can be challenging. Here are some steps to consider:\n\n1. **Acknowledge Your Feelings**: It's normal to feel hurt or conflicted. Allow yourself to process these emotions before taking any action.\n\n2. **Communicate Openly**: If you feel comfortable, talk to your friend about how you feel. Be honest but also respectful of their relationship. Avoid blaming or accusing them, as this can lead to tension.\n\n3. **Give Yourself Space**: If the situation becomes overwhelming, it might help to give yourself a little distance from both your friend and your crush. This can help you gain perspective and reduce any feelings of jealousy.\n\n4. **Shift Your Focus**: Redirect your attention to other friendships, hobbies, or interests. Engaging in activities you enjoy can help take your mind off the situation.\n\n5. **Respect Their Relationship**: If your friend and crush are happy together, it's important to respect their relationship. Trying to interfere could lead to more hurt feelings.\n\n6. **Reflect on Your Feelings**: Consider whether your crush is worth pursuing further or if it might be a good time to move on. Sometimes, having feelings for someone can cloud judgment.\n\n7. **Talk to Someone Else**: If you're struggling with your emotions, consider speaking to a trusted friend or family member for support and perspective.\n\nUltimately, it\u2019s important to prioritize your own well-being and the friendship. Whatever you choose to do, ensure it's respectful to everyone involved.",
